<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-08T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="971" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d971">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/1160: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08T19:00:00-04:00">November
                                    8, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>97. With reference to the British plan to supply Saudi Arabia with the
                            military equipment described in Department’s 92, October 23,<note n="4" xml:id="d971fn4">See footnote 99, <ref target="#pg_908">p.
                                908</ref>.</note> please inform us whether Ibn Saud or other Saudi
                            Arabian officials approached the British in regard to such supplies and,
                            if so, the circumstances under which the approach was made. Please state
                            also whether any of this equipment has been delivered by the
                                British.<note n="4a" xml:id="d971fn4a">For a British report
                                regarding the approach by Mr. Moose to the Saudi Arabian Government
                                pursuant to this instruction, and comment by Mr. Moose thereon, see
                                    <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_378">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at
                                    Cairo and Tehran, 1943, pp. 378</ref> and <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_447">447</ref>; for the Minister
                                Resident’s reply to the Department on November 19, see telegram No.
                                189, <ref target="#pg_912">p. 912</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>